reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 27, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for gaming, power efficient!
reviews.reviewText: 7w power draw at idle, great gaming performance, easy to cool, can't ask for more.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 5, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great CPU for the price
reviews.reviewText: I bought this on Black Friday for $200, and for that price it's fantastic. This was my first PC build and it works great. Definitely recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 25, 2023
reviews.reviewText: This cpu is great, even in 2023 it’s a great cpu for gaming. The only downside is that it doesn’t have any integrated gpu if you ever need to troubleshoot but realistically, it’s not a huge deal. It’s worth getting even going into 2024, the changes haven’t been drastic enough to spend the absurd amount for modern cpus. If you can get a 13600k instead or even 14600k, go that route but if you’re on a heavy budget, buy this.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Just a fantastic cpu overall
reviews.reviewText: Don't be suckers. The i9 is a workstation cpu and you don't need that for your gaming pc. The i7 is the way. Fantastic overall. 12th gen so far has been the best gen (13th was a half step and 14th is a joke)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 8, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I installed this CPU in my first gaming PC build, and it has way more than enough processing power for what I do. Great value; would buy again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 3, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Lost for words, even right now with 14th gen already on the market, this is a great choice for those who still want an 8 core cpu for multitasking, just make sure to get a really good and trustworthy 80 plus gold PSU or higher, you'll have to take good care of your graphics card because this chip doesn't have integrated graphics

reviews.reviewTitle: Major upgrade for me so my review only goes so far.
reviews.reviewText: I'm upgrading from an old AMD FX 8320 chip and that was an 8 core 8 thread 3.5ghz cpu. i could overclock it to 4ghz no problem but it was DDR3 1600mhz ram. This thing crush's that chip like there is no tomorrow. I have this chip paired with Corsair Vengeance DDR5 5200 RAM, a Asus TUF Z690,1X Fire Cuda 530 Gen 4 NVMe SSD, Alseye M120D cooler and a case with 7 fans, crushed 4tb data file transfers across old drives in about 12 hours, never got hotter then 62C in any of my bench tests and maintains an average temp of 35C while general use. startup is 0-15C until you heat it up first time then it doesn't seem to drop below 32 until a shut down for a while. I had it off all day on second day, turned it on and logged in, got distracted on my cell phone for 1 hour then looked at temp, and it was 12C. checked 3 different sources all read same. then i ran a game for 15 mins and it got to 43C. i stopped the game and left it for an hour to see what it did with nothing really running. it immediately dropped to 36 when i shut game off within under 5 seconds.After 20 mins of it pegged at 36 i maxed out the fans then took the hour to drop to 32 to see if it made a difference. 0 change. anyway Skoocum chip and it isn't even the best you can get right now. plus gen 14 is right around corner ;)
